<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I for one have recently noticed that Beethovens Eroica symphony ends with the same two ‘hits’ it had at the very beginning of the first movement. I can’t appreciate this enough and it genuinely made me cry thinking how genius that was after such a monster of a symphony.</p> <p>What other details have you noticed in a composers work that you love?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/0neMoreYear"> /u/0neMoreYear </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wgoebm/what_is_your_favorite_small_detail_about_a_piece/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wgoebm/what_is_your_favorite_small_detail_about_a_piece/">[comments]</a></span>